Scale Up

Diagram
User → DNS → HAProxy 1 + HAProxy 2 (cluster) →
Web Server → Application Server → Database Server

Added components
- Additional server: the infrastructure is divided into separate layers, giving each service its own dedicated resources.
- HAProxy cluster: using multiple load balancers improves availability and eliminates a single point of failure at that level.
- Service separation: the web server, application server, and database are deployed on different machines.

Purpose of these changes
- Dedicated web server: efficiently handles incoming HTTP/HTTPS requests.
- Dedicated application server: processes business logic without sharing resources with other services.
- Dedicated database server: improves performance, data management, and simplifies maintenance.
- Load balancer cluster: ensures better traffic distribution and higher availability.

Benefits
- This architecture improves scalability, as each layer (web, application, database) can be scaled independently based on traffic and resource needs.